"But what if they *are* real?" they say quietly.

You missed it. The swords are real. The trap is real. And you just told them it wasn't.

-> Sasha.Session1.Position2.End

# --- Five of Cups ---

:: Sasha.Session1.Position2.FiveCups

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} [EXCELLENT: "You're grieving something that isn't dead yet. That's the hardest kind."] -> Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [EXCELLENT: Observe the math — three cups spilled, two standing. What's the ratio in their life?] -> Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.ExcellentAnalytical
+ [GOOD: "The Five of Cups is about loss. But not all the cups are empty."] -> Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.Good
+ [OKAY: "This card represents grief and disappointment."] -> Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.Okay
+ [BAD: "This card means you've lost something, but you'll get over it."] -> Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.Bad

:: Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(2)
~ sasha.discussed_relationship = True
"You're grieving something that isn't dead yet," you say. {cards[1].reversed ? "And you've started to turn around — to see what's still standing behind you. But turning around means facing what you've been avoiding." | "That's the hardest kind of grief. You can't mourn something that's still technically alive. So instead you just... carry it. The weight of something that should be beautiful but isn't."}

The room goes very still.

Sasha's hand moves to their wrist — to a braided leather bracelet. They twist it, once, twice.

"Somebody made you that bracelet," you say, before you can stop yourself.

"Yeah," Sasha whispers.

-> Sasha.Session1.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session1.P2.Five.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
