:: Sasha.Session1.P3.Seven.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(2)
~ sasha.discussed_jordan = True
~ sasha.discussed_pattern = True
"Someone is taking pieces of you," you say, {cards[2].reversed ? "and you've started to notice. The reversed Seven — the deception is visible now. You can see what's been taken." | "and calling it love. Five swords taken, two left behind. Your time, your energy, your confidence, your friendships, your sense of self. And what did they leave you? Just enough to keep you from noticing what's gone."}

Sasha's hand goes to the bracelet. Jordan's bracelet. Their eyes are full.

"This is Jordan," they whisper. Not a question. "This is what it's been like."

"I know," you say. "I've been watching you disappear for months. I just didn't know how to say it."

"Nobody does." They wipe their eyes. "Nobody knows how to say it because I made *damn* sure nobody could see it."

-> Sasha.Session1.Position3.End

:: Sasha.Session1.P3.Seven.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
~ sasha.discussed_jordan = True
"Five swords taken," you say. {cards[2].reversed ? "But the reversed card means the theft is becoming visible. Let me name them:" | "Let me count what's been taken."} "Your time — do you have less of it than you used to? Your friendships — have people drifted? Your confidence — do you second-guess yourself more now than two years ago?"

"Stop," Sasha says. But gently. "Yeah. All of that. Since I moved in with Jordan it's just—"

They catch themselves. But it's too late.

"I know," you say quietly. "I've noticed."

"You've *noticed?*"

"You stopped inviting me over. You stopped texting first. You second-guess everything now. That's not the Sasha I know."

They don't answer. Which is an answer.

-> Sasha.Session1.Position3.End

:: Sasha.Session1.P3.Seven.Good
