-> Sasha.Session1.Position3.End

# --- Position 3 Convergence ---

:: Sasha.Session1.Position3.End
Three cards on the cloth. The story is becoming clear — to you, and to Sasha.

@if sasha.discussed_jordan:
    The truth about Jordan is in the room now. Not Jordan the person — you already knew Jordan. But the *real* Jordan. The one behind the "we're great" texts and the dinner party smile.

    Sasha sits with it. They look tired — not exhausted, but *relieved*. Like carrying a secret weighs something and they just put it down.

    "One more card?" they ask.
@elif sasha.discussed_relationship:
    They haven't said Jordan's name. But they've acknowledged the shape of it — the relationship, the wrongness, the weight.

    "Last card," you say.
@else:
    The reading has been surface-level. Sasha's guard held. But the last card is the one that matters most.

    "Last one," you say.
@endif

-> Sasha.Session1.Position4Hub

# ============================================================================
# POSITION 4: WHAT YOU NEED
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session1.Position4Hub
@render render_reading(reading=reading)

**Position 4: What You Need — What Would Actually Help Right Now**

**{cards[3].get_display_name()}**

@if cards[3].name == "The Star":
    The Star. A figure kneels by water, pouring from two vessels. Stars shine overhead. Hope. Healing. The light that comes after the tower falls.

    @if cards[3].reversed:
        Reversed: the hope is there but buried. You've lost faith in the possibility of better.
    @endif

    Sasha looks at the card and their breath catches. It's the most beautiful card in the spread — quiet, luminous, tender.

    "That's pretty," they say, voice thick.

    "It is," you say. {cards[3].reversed ? "But reversed, The Star is hope you've stopped believing in. You need to find it again." | "The Star is what the cards want for you, Sasha. Hope. Healing. The knowledge that you deserve something gentler than what you have."}

    -> Sasha.Session1.Position4.Star
@else:
    Strength. A figure gently holds open the jaws of a lion. Not with force — with patience, with tenderness, with an unshakeable quiet conviction.

    @if cards[3].reversed:
        Reversed: the courage is there, but you've forgotten you have it.
    @endif

    Sasha studies the card. "That person is... petting a lion?"

    "Holding it open," you say. {cards[3].reversed ? "Reversed: you have this strength inside you. But you've forgotten. Someone convinced you that you're not brave." | "Not with muscles. With patience and courage. The quiet kind of bravery that doesn't shout."}

    -> Sasha.Session1.Position4.Strength
@endif

# --- The Star ---

:: Sasha.Session1.Position4.Star

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} [EXCELLENT: "You need to remember that you deserve tenderness. Not just for other people — for yourself."] -> Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [EXCELLENT: Frame the Star as a specific action plan — what healing looks like in practice] -> Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.ExcellentAnalytical
+ [GOOD: "The Star says you need hope. Real hope, not the kind you perform."] -> Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.Good
+ [OKAY: "The Star represents hope and healing."] -> Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.Okay

:: Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(2)
~ sasha.discussed_fear = True
"You need to remember that you deserve tenderness," you say. {cards[3].reversed ? "But reversed — you've stopped believing that. Someone has been telling you, in a thousand small ways, that what you have is the best you can get. And you believed them. You need to *unbelieve* them." | "Not the kind you give everyone else. The kind you give *yourself.* The Star is pouring from two vessels — one into the water, one onto the ground. You've been pouring for others so long you forgot you need to pour for yourself too."}

Sasha starts crying.

Not big, dramatic crying. Just — tears, running silently down their face, while they sit very still with their hands in their lap.

"I'm sorry," they say automatically.

"Don't be sorry. This is what the cards are for."

They nod. Wipe their face with their sleeve. Take a shaky breath.

"I came here for *practice,*" they say, half-laughing, half-crying. "This was supposed to be *easy.*"

"It was supposed to be what you needed."

"...Yeah. I think it was."

-> Sasha.Session1.Position4.End

:: Sasha.Session1.P4.Star.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
~ sasha.discussed_fear = True
"The Star is specific," you say. {cards[3].reversed ? "Reversed, it means the *capacity* for hope exists but you've blocked it. Practically: when's the last time you did something just for yourself? Not for Jordan, not for your friends, not for work. Just for *you*?" | "It's not 'hope' in the vague sense. It's a prescription. You need: space to feel without performing. Honest conversation with someone who isn't invested in keeping you where you are. And time to remember who you were before this relationship started defining you."}

Sasha blinks. "That's... really specific."

"The cards are specific when you're ready to hear it."

Tears come. Quiet ones.

"I don't even remember," they say. "Who I was before Jordan. Isn't that messed up? It's only been two years and I can't remember."

"That's not messed up. That's a symptom."

-> Sasha.Session1.Position4.End

