:: Sasha.Session1.Synth.Transformational
~ sasha.add_trust(15)
~ reader.add_empathy(1)
Sasha sits back. Wrung out. But lighter.

"Okay. *Okay.*" They press their palms against their eyes. "I came here thinking this was going to be, like, 'you'll meet a tall dark stranger' and instead you just — I don't even know what just happened."

"The cards happened."

"*You* happened." They look at you with a new kind of respect. "I've been carrying this for... a really long time. And nobody saw it. I'm *good* at hiding it. And you just—"

They gesture at the spread.

"Four cards," you say.

"Four cards," they repeat, shaking their head. "Unreal."

@if sasha.discussed_jordan:
    "I need to figure out what to do about Jordan," they say. The sentence is steady. Clear. Like they've been rehearsing it in their head for months and only just now let it out of their mouth.

    "That's a reading for another day."

    "Can I come back? For real? Not practice?"

    "Of course."
@else:
    "There's... something I need to deal with. I wasn't ready to name it today. But I want to come back and actually talk about it."

    "The cards will be here."

    "Good. Because *I'll* be here."
@endif

-> Sasha.Session1.Departure

:: Sasha.Session1.Synth.Profound
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
Sasha nods slowly, looking at the cards.

"That was... a lot more than I expected."

"The cards tend to find what matters."

"Yeah, they found it alright." They rub their face. "I don't know what to do with all this. But I know I need to sit with it."

@if sasha.discussed_jordan:
    "And I need to think about Jordan. About what you said."
@endif

"I'd like to come back," they say. "If that's okay."

"More than okay."

-> Sasha.Session1.Departure

:: Sasha.Session1.Synth.Helpful
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
"That was interesting," Sasha says. Carefully. Like they're weighing how much to admit.

"Interesting good or interesting bad?"

"Interesting... real." They fidget with the bracelet. "More real than I thought it would be."

A pause.

"Can I come back? I think I want to do this again. For real."

"Anytime."

-> Sasha.Session1.Departure

:: Sasha.Session1.Synth.Adequate
"Huh," Sasha says.

Not overwhelmed. Not transformed. Just... something to chew on.

"That was... okay. Some of it hit. Some of it didn't."

"Readings aren't always lightning bolts. Sometimes they're seeds."

They almost smile. "Poetic. Okay, I'll give you another shot. Can I come back next week?"

"Absolutely."

-> Sasha.Session1.Departure

:: Sasha.Session1.Synth.Mediocre
Sasha stands up. Stretches.

"Well. That was... something."

The air between you is polite. Distant. The reading didn't land. You know it. They know it.

"Thanks for letting me practice," you say.

"Sure, dude. Anytime." But the brightness is hollow and you both know it.

They won't be back. You can feel it.

-> Sasha.Session1.Departure

# ============================================================================
# DEPARTURE
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session1.Departure
Sasha stands. Stretches. Puts their shoes on.

@if session.reading_quality in ["transformational", "profound"]:
    At the door, they pause. Turn back.

    "Hey. Thank you. For real. Not 'thanks for the tarot.' Thanks for — seeing me."

    They pull the thermos out of their bag. "Keep the coffee. You earned it."

    ~ reader.add_money(0)  // Friends don't charge friends
    ~ session.payment = 0

    "Sasha — you don't owe me anything. This was practice, remember?"

    "Yeah, well." They smile. Small, real, a little broken. "Best practice I ever did."
@elif session.reading_quality == "helpful":
    At the door, Sasha pauses. "Hey. That was good. You're better at this than you think."

    "That means a lot coming from my guinea pig."

    "Ha. See you next week."

    ~ reader.add_money(0)
    ~ session.payment = 0
@elif session.reading_quality == "adequate":
    At the door: "Same time next week?"

    "Sure."

    "Cool. I'll bring better snacks."

    ~ reader.add_money(0)
    ~ session.payment = 0
@else:
    At the door, Sasha waves. "Thanks, babe. Good luck with the card thing."

    The door closes.

    ~ reader.add_money(0)
    ~ session.payment = 0

    You sit in the quiet, staring at four cards that didn't do their job. Or maybe you didn't do yours.
@endif

-> Sasha.Session1.End

# ============================================================================
# SESSION END
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session1.End
@py:
# Save session results
sasha.session_one_quality = session.reading_quality
sasha.session_one_cards = cards
sasha.sessions_completed += 1
reader.sessions_completed += 1
@endpy

@if sasha.will_return:
    The door closes. The apartment is quiet.

    You gather the cards, but you don't shuffle them right away. You just hold them.

    Sasha came in for practice. They left with something heavier and more precious: the beginning of honesty.

    @if sasha.discussed_jordan:
        *Jordan.* You knew Jordan. You liked Jordan, or the version of Jordan you were shown. But what you know now is bigger than dinner party charm — you know the shape of what Jordan has taken from your friend, and the shape their absence will leave when Sasha is ready to fill it with themselves.
    @endif

    You put the cards away. Wash the French press. Eat the rest of the trail mix.

    Your phone buzzes.

    **[Text from: Sasha]**
    @if session.reading_quality == "transformational":
        *"ok so i cried in my car for like 20 minutes and now im at trader joes buying ice cream. thank u for breaking me open i think?? same time next week??"*
    @elif session.reading_quality == "profound":
        *"that was intense. in a good way. i think. see u next week?"*
    @else:
        *"hey. thanks. can we do that again sometime?"*
    @endif

    You smile.

    **[Session 1 Complete — Sasha will return]**
@else:
    The door closes.

    You gather the cards. Shuffle them back into the deck.

    The reading didn't land. Sasha left lighter than they came, but not by much. Some readings are like that — the cards show up but the reader doesn't.

    You file it away. Learn from it. Get better.

    **[Session 1 Complete — Sasha will not return]**
@endif

